{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"303ade33-5142-4c8a-9396-64fefa799ab3","content":"On macOS, when a NativeAOT app crashes, look for **Apple's built-in crash reports**:\n\n1. **Crash reports directory:**\n   ```\n   ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   ```\n   Files are named like `YourApp_<date>_<host>.ips` (or `.crash` on older macOS).\n\n2. **Console.app** → sidebar → *Crash Reports* — lets you browse and search them.\n\n3. **Core dumps** (if enabled):\n   ```bash\n   ulimit -c unlimited   # enable before running\n   ```\n   Cores land in `/cores/core.<pid>`.\n\nThe `.ips` crash report includes the faulting thread, backtrace, and signal info — usually enough to start debugging without `createdump`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3689b3ab-673d-4d2e-853c-493616460fa3","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS, without `createdump`. This is a general knowledge question - no code changes or repo exploration needed.","outputTokens":253,"requestId":"942A:A7934:243E34:2B5143:69E81FC9"},"id":"374d0991-843b-4fa6-9fe2-5f9cd4911830","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:09:36.795Z","parentId":"b3dd1084-18f4-4847-819b-6f7565419dd3"}
